# Email Provider Adapters Module

## PURPOSE
Contains email provider-specific implementations (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo).
Each provider follows the same interface for consistency.

## CONTAINS
- gmail.js: Gmail API integration
- outlook.js: Outlook/Hotmail integration (future)
- yahoo.js: Yahoo Mail integration (future)
- base-provider.js: Abstract base class/interface

## RESPONSIBILITIES
- Implement provider-specific authentication
- Fetch emails using provider APIs
- Parse provider-specific email formats
- Extract subscription data and unsubscribe links
- Handle provider-specific rate limits and errors

## INTERFACE REQUIREMENTS
Each provider must implement:
- authenticate(): Promise<token>
- searchEmails(query): Promise<emails[]>
- getEmailDetails(emailId): Promise<emailData>
- extractUnsubscribeLink(email): string|null

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /src/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Used by: /src/core/scanner.js

## RULES
- All providers must implement the same interface
- Provider-specific logic stays in this module only
- Use OAuth2 for authentication where possible
- Handle API errors and rate limits gracefully
